sentences.s: Schedule Daily/Weekly Group Facebook Threads with Images Using Google Calendar + Buffer Automatically add daily or weekly threads with IMAGES  to your Facebook Group via BUFFER.
Simply create a Google Calendar Event Titled "BUFFER THIS TO FB GROUP" Put image url in the "Where" select then write your post in the "Description" area.
Set the REPEAT Function on Google Calendar so it automatically shoves posts to BUFFER on the right day of the week.
(Yay for setting it and forgetting it!)
(To get an image url - upload images to your site as media files or add them to google drive)
*Note: When this event is triggered it will slide your post into the next available BUFFER slot for that account*
***Remember IFTTT only works with ONE of the accounts You Control with Buffer.
Made sure it's set to the Facebook Group you want and not your Twitter or FB Business Page***

app: Schedule Daily/Weekly Group Facebook Threads with Images Using Google Calendar + Buffer
description:
Schedule Daily/Weekly Group Facebook Threads with Images Using Google Calendar + Buffer Automatically add daily or weekly threads with IMAGES  to your Facebook Group via BUFFER.  

Simply create a Google Calendar Event Titled "BUFFER THIS TO FB GROUP" Put image url in the "Where" select then write your post in the "Description" area. 

Set the REPEAT Function on Google Calendar so it automatically shoves posts to BUFFER on the right day of the week. (Yay for setting it and forgetting it!)  

(To get an image url - upload images to your site as media files or add them to google drive) 

*Note: When this event is triggered it will slide your post into the next available BUFFER slot for that account*

***Remember IFTTT only works with ONE of the accounts You Control with Buffer. Made sure it's set to the Facebook Group you want and not your Twitter or FB Business Page***

sentences.s: Use Google Calendar to Publish Facebook Page Status and Set to Repeat Directions: You need to use one Google Calendar for each Facebook page you own.
It also has to be from your main calendar, not additional calendar within your main calendar.
(Step 1) - Create a new event in Google Calendar with the title #fbstatus
(Step 2) - Type your status message in the event's "Description" field and hit save.
(Step 3) - Schedule your "event" to repeat as often as desired.
The trigger will fire within 15 minutes of the starting time of an "event" on your Google Calendar that contains the #fbstatus.
It will then create a new plain text status message on your Facebook Page.
If you include links in the message area they will be clickable on your page.
That's it!

app: Use Google Calendar to Publish Facebook Page Status and Set to Repeat
description:
Use Google Calendar to Publish Facebook Page Status and Set to Repeat Directions: You need to use one Google Calendar for each Facebook page you own. It also has to be from your main calendar, not additional calendar within your main calendar. 
(Step 1) - Create a new event in Google Calendar with the title #fbstatus 
(Step 2) - Type your status message in the event's "Description" field and hit save.
(Step 3) - Schedule your "event" to repeat as often as desired. 

The trigger will fire within 15 minutes of the starting time of an "event" on your Google Calendar that contains the #fbstatus.    It will then create a new plain text status message on your Facebook Page.  If you include links in the message area they will be clickable on your page. 

That's it!
